A recently-imposed ban restricting large cruise ships from passing through Italy’s historic city of Venice has been lifted.

The city’s regional court of appeal overturned the regulations, which were only implemented in November, and which prevented all ships over 96,000 gross tons from sailing along the Guidecca Canal to the city’s main cruise terminal.

It also limited the number of ships over 40,000 gross tonnes from sailing along the route to just five a day.

